        /* OPSEC & Privacy FAQ */
        opsec_title: "OPSEC & Privacy Questions",
        opsec_q1: "What metadata does PassForge store?",
        opsec_a1: "PassForge stores: Vault location path, Last access timestamp, Language preference, Theme selection. NOT stored: IP addresses, usage analytics, telemetry, cloud sync data. All sensitive metadata (entry titles, URLs, usernames) is encrypted within the vault.",
        opsec_q2: "Does PassForge work on Linux/macOS?",
        opsec_a2: "Partially. PassForge is primarily designed for Windows or linux. macOS compatibility requires modifications: Remove UAC elevation code, Replace Windows-specific APIs (ctypes.windll), Adjust file path handling. Core cryptography (PBKDF2, Fernet, bcrypt) is cross-platform compatible.",
        opsec_q3: "Can I use PassForge completely offline?",
        opsec_a3: "Yes, 100%. PassForge makes ZERO network calls. No telemetry, no update checks, no cloud sync, no analytics. The application is designed for air-gapped environments and operates entirely locally.",
        opsec_q4: "What forensic traces are left after use?",
        opsec_a4: "Minimal but not zero: Vault database file (.db), Config file (vault_settings.json), Python cache files (__pycache__). NOT left: Plaintext passwords, Decrypted data, Session keys, Clipboard history (auto-cleared). For maximum forensic resistance, use Tails OS or encrypted RAM disk.",
        opsec_q5: "Are vault backups also encrypted?",
        opsec_a5: "Yes. Backup files are identical copies of the encrypted vault database. Without the master password, backups are useless encrypted blobs. Recommendation: Store backups on encrypted USB drives in geographically distributed locations.",
        opsec_q6: "How to safely import/export data?",
        opsec_a6: "Export: Use built-in export to encrypted JSON. Import: Verify file integrity before import, Use separate vault for untrusted imports, Never import plaintext CSV on shared computers. Best practice: Manual re-entry for maximum security.",
        opsec_q7: "Does PassForge support plausible deniability?",
        opsec_a7: "No. PassForge does not support hidden vaults or decoy passwords. For plausible deniability, use VeraCrypt hidden volumes to store the entire vault file. This provides OS-level deniability independent of PassForge.",
        opsec_q8: "Are user actions logged?",
        opsec_a8: "No. PassForge does not maintain audit logs, access logs, or activity history. This is intentional for privacy. If you need audit trails, implement OS-level file access monitoring externally.",

