        audit_exec_h: "Executive Summary",
        audit_exec_p: "Overall Security Level: ‚ö†Ô∏è Medium. PassForge implements cryptographically sound primitives but lacks enterprise-grade memory protection and privilege management. Suitable for individual offline use, NOT recommended for high-security enterprise environments without modifications.",
        audit_high_h: "üî¥ High-Risk Findings",
        audit_high_1: "1. Automatic Privilege Escalation - Program requests admin rights on every launch (OWASP A5: Security Misconfiguration). KeePass/Bitwarden never auto-elevate.",
        audit_high_2: "2. Memory Key Residue - Python immutable strings/bytes cannot be securely erased from RAM. Risk of memory dump attacks (OWASP A2: Cryptographic Failures).",
        audit_high_3: "3. Single-Point Encryption - Fernet uses single key. If compromised, entire vault decrypts instantly. No additional integrity layers.",
